                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm always coming but never here.
<br />
To some I bring a new, to others a fear.
<br />
And when I've come and gone
<br />
Another is always soon to follow.
<br />

<br />
Then again, if you answer this, won't everyone know it and our poor griffion friend will continue to go hungry?
<br />

<br />
(Btw, this was ripped off from a friend of mine, who may or may not have made it up himself, I'm sure his version was better)
<br />

<br />
P.S.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
A man walks up to you and says - "everything I say to you is a lie."
<br />
Is he telling you the truth or is he lying? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Thats a paradox, not a riddle. The diffrence being riddles tend to have actual answers.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
