                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Vizier wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Heres an easy one:
<br />

<br />
A man walks up to you and says - "everything I say to you is a lie."
<br />
Is he telling you the truth or is he lying?
<br />

<br />
Justify your answer.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
He's lying.  Since he's lying, you know that not everything he says is a lie.  However, because that statement is a lie doesn't necessarily make the opposite true, that everything he says is the truth.  If he tells some lies and some truths, this statement is still a lie.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=892405" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Jetta Starr</a>, Gnome Phantasmist
